<item>
            <title>[PIG-2714] Pig documentation on TOP funcation has issues </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2714</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following documentation gives a picture that the columns are indexed from 1 but is actually indexed from 0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://pig.apache.org/docs/r0.8.1/piglatin_ref2.html#TOP&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://pig.apache.org/docs/r0.8.1/piglatin_ref2.html#TOP&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Specifically on the sample code snippet&lt;br/&gt;
result = TOP(10, 2, C); // and retain top 10 occurrences of &apos;second&apos; in first&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;second&apos; is the second column, in that case we need to have the TOP function as TOP(10, 1, C) instead of TOP(10, 2, C)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
